                  S. Ambr. de Sacerd. dignit. c 1. receaued their Pastorall authority ouer their flocks, with S. Peter: and therfore he saith, Quas oues, &amp; quem gregem non solùm tunc Beatus Petrus suscepit, sed &amp; cum, illo eas nos suscepimus omnes: Which sheep, and which flock not only the Blessed Peter then receaued, but as so

we all receaued them with him. Thus saith S. Ambrose, which all Catholikes do graunt and teach in like mā
